summary:
Tuesday, February 26th, 2019
Stress Management Techniques
tea time - ginger ✔️
Aromatherapy - Eden Garden’s “Meditation” ✔️
deep...
body:
Tuesday, February 26th, 2019

Stress Management Techniques

tea time - ginger ✔️

Aromatherapy - Eden Garden’s “Meditation” ✔️

deep breathing/meditation - Headspace for 10 minutes ✔️

stick to fucking bedtime (you God damn fool) ✔️

neck and shoulder stretches ✔️

Habits

limit of two caffeinated beverages - 16 oz drip coffee ✔️

go back to sleep after my inevitable bathroom break - why? ❌

journal ✔️

tidy up at least one thing/place in the house - dishes, cooking, tons of adulting ✔️

lightbox ✔️

Medication Taken

Rx– Zoloft ✔️

Digestive + Malabsorption– Probiotic, Iron/B12/Folate ✔️

Migraine– Magnesium, cucumerin, CoQ10, CBD oil ✔️

Nutrition

Workouts and Activities Done

For the first time in months, I felt well enough to run. It wasn’t fast and it wasn’t for long. I think I probably only got 9 minutes total of running out of this treadmill session. I wanted to get my heart rate up, but I didn’t want to get to the point where you get that horrible burn in your throat. I’m going to try and slowly work back up to my pace. I use to run close to 6mi/hr pretty alright. I also appeared to walk an absolute shit ton. Wasn’t intentional. Just one of those days!

Mental and Menstrual Moments
